#, no-c-format
msgid "Bits.ALIGNMENT_TOP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: parameter
#: part1-layout.xml:1735
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bits.ALIGNMENT_VERTICAL_CENTER"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: parameter
#: part1-layout.xml:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bits.ALIGNMENT_BOTTOM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1744
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can determine the current alignment of a component with <methodname>getComponentAlignment()</methodname>, which returns an <classname>Alignment</classname> object. The class provides a number of getter methods for decoding the alignment, which you can also get as a bitmask value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1753
#, no-c-format
msgid "Size of Aligned Components"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can only align a component that is smaller than its containing cell in the direction of alignment. If a component has 100% width, as many components have by default, horizontal alignment does not have any effect. For example, <classname>Label</classname> is 100% wide by default and can not therefore be horizontally aligned as such. The problem can be hard to notice, as the text inside a <classname>Label</classname> is left-aligned."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1765
#, no-c-format
msgid "You usually need to set either a fixed size, undefined size, or less than a 100% relative size for the component to be aligned - a size that is smaller than the containing layout has."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1771
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, assuming that a <classname>Label</classname> has short content that is less wide than the containing <classname>VerticalLayout</classname>, you could center it as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1777
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<?pocket-size 65% ?><![CDATA[VerticalLayout layout = new VerticalLayout(); // 100% default width\n"
      "Label label = new Label(\"Hello\"); // 100% default width\n"
      "label.setSizeUndefined();\n"
      "layout.addComponent(label);\n"
      "layout.setComponentAlignment(label, Alignment.MIDDLE_CENTER);]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1779
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set the size as undefined and the component itself contains components, make sure that the contained components also have either undefined or fixed size. For example, if you set the size of a <classname>Form</classname> as undefined, its containing layout <classname>FormLayout</classname> has 100% default width, which you also need to set as undefined. But then, any components inside the <classname>FormLayout</classname> must have either undefined or fixed size."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1796
#, no-c-format
msgid "Layout Cell Spacing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1798
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <classname>VerticalLayout</classname>, <classname>HorizontalLayout</classname>, and <classname>GridLayout</classname> layouts offer a <methodname>setSpacing()</methodname> method for enabling space between the cells in the layout. Enabling the spacing adds a spacing style for all cells except the first so that, by setting the left or top padding, you can specify the amount of spacing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1808
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enable spacing, simply call <methodname>setSpacing(true)</methodname> for the layout as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<![CDATA[HorizontalLayout layout2 = new HorizontalLayout();\n"
      "layout2.addStyleName(\"spacingexample\");\n"
      "layout2.setSpacing(true);\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 1\"));\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 2\"));\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 3\"));\n"
      "\n"
      "VerticalLayout layout4 = new VerticalLayout();\n"
      "layout4.addStyleName(\"spacingexample\");\n"
      "layout4.setSpacing(true);\n"
      "layout4.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 1\"));\n"
      "layout4.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 2\"));\n"
      "layout4.addComponent(new Button(\"Component 3\"));]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1815
#, no-c-format
msgid "In practise, the <methodname>setSpacing()</methodname> method toggles between the \"<literal>v-COMPONENTCLASSNAME-spacing-on</literal>\" and \"<literal>-off</literal>\" CSS class names in the cell elements. Elements having those class names can be used to define the spacing metrics in a theme."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1823
#, no-c-format
msgid "The layouts have a spacing style name to define spacing also when spacing is off. This allows you to define a small default spacing between components by default and a larger one when the spacing is actually enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1830
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spacing can be horizontal (for <classname>HorizontalLayout</classname>), vertical (for <classname>VerticalLayout</classname>), or both (for <classname>GridLayout</classname>). The name of the spacing style for horizontal and vertical spacing is the base name of the component style name plus the \"<literal>-spacing-on</literal>\" suffix, as shown in the following table:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1840
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spacing Style Names"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: classname
#: part1-layout.xml:1844
#, no-c-format
msgid "VerticalLayout"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: part1-layout.xml:1845
#, no-c-format
msgid "v-verticallayout-spacing-on"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: classname
#: part1-layout.xml:1848
#, no-c-format
msgid "HorizontalLayout"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: part1-layout.xml:1849
#, no-c-format
msgid "v-horizontallayout-spacing-on"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: part1-layout.xml:1853
#, no-c-format
msgid "v-gridlayout-spacing-on"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1859
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the CSS example below, we specify the exact amount of spacing for the code example given above, for the layouts with the custom \"<literal>spacingexample</literal>\" style:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1865
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<?pocket-size 65% ?><![CDATA[/* Set the amount of horizontal cell spacing in a\n"
      " * specific element with the \"-spacingexample\" style. */\n"
      ".v-horizontallayout-spacingexample .v-horizontallayout-spacing-on {\n"
      "    padding-left: 30px;\n"
      "}\n"
      "\n"
      "/* Set the amount of vertical cell spacing in a\n"
      " * specific element with the \"-spacingexample\" style. */\n"
      ".v-verticallayout-spacingexample .v-verticallayout-spacing-on {\n"
      "    padding-top: 30px;\n"
      "}\n"
      "\n"
      "/* Set the amount of both vertical and horizontal cell spacing\n"
      " * in a specific element with the \"-spacingexample\" style. */\n"
      ".v-gridlayout-spacingexample .v-gridlayout-spacing-on {\n"
      "    padding-top: 30px;\n"
      "    padding-left: 50px;\n"
      "}]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1867
#, no-c-format
msgid "The resulting layouts will look as shown in <xref linkend=\"figure.layout.spacing\"/>, which also shows the layouts with no spacing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1874
#, no-c-format
msgid "Layout Spacings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1886
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spacing is unrelated to \"cell spacing\" in HTML tables. While many layout components are implemented with HTML tables in the browser, this implementation is not guaranteed to stay the same and at least <classname>Vertical</classname>-/<classname>HorizontalLayout</classname> could be implemented with <literal>&lt;div&gt;</literal> elements as well. In fact, as GWT compiles widgets separately for different browsers, the implementation could even vary between browsers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1895
#, no-c-format
msgid "Also note that HTML elements with spacing classnames don't necessarily exist in a component after rendering, because the Client-Side Engine of Vaadin processes them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1904 part1-layout.xml:1962
#, no-c-format
msgid "Layout Margins"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1906
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, layout components do not have any margin around them. You can add margin with CSS directly to the layout component. Below we set margins for a specific layout component (here a <literal>horizontallayout</literal>):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1912
#, no-c-format
msgid "<![CDATA[layout1.addStyleName(\"marginexample1\");]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1913
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      ".v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-marginexample1\n"
      "        .v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-margin {\n"
      "        padding-left:   200px;\n"
      "        padding-right:  100px;\n"
      "        padding-top:    50px;\n"
      "        padding-bottom: 25px;\n"
      "}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1915
#, no-c-format
msgid "Similar settings exist for other layouts such as <literal>verticallayout</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1919
#, no-c-format
msgid "The layout size calculations require the margins to be defined as CSS <literal>padding</literal> rather than as CSS <literal>margin</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1925
#, no-c-format
msgid "As an alternative to the pure CSS method, you can set up a margin around the layout that can be enabled with <methodname>setMargin(true)</methodname>. The margin element has some default margin widths, but you can adjust the widths in CSS if you need to."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1932
#, no-c-format
msgid "Let us consider the following example, where we enable the margin on all sides of the layout:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<![CDATA[// Create a layout\n"
      "HorizontalLayout layout2 = new HorizontalLayout();\n"
      "containinglayout.addComponent(\n"
      "    new Label(\"Layout with margin on all sides:\"));\n"
      "containinglayout.addComponent(layout2);\n"
      "        \n"
      "// Set style name for the layout to allow styling it\n"
      "layout2.addStyleName(\"marginexample\");\n"
      "        \n"
      "// Have margin on all sides around the layout\n"
      "layout2.setMargin(true);\n"
      "        \n"
      "// Put something inside the layout\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Label(\"Cell 1\"));\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Label(\"Cell 2\"));\n"
      "layout2.addComponent(new Label(\"Cell 3\"));]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1939
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can enable the margins only for specific sides. The margins are specified for the <methodname>setMargin()</methodname> method in clockwise order for top, right, bottom, and left margin. The following would enable the top and left margins:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1946
#, no-c-format
msgid "<![CDATA[layout2.setMargin(true, false, false, true);]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1948
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can specify the actual margin widths in the CSS if you are not satisfied with the default widths (in this example for a <classname>HorizontalLayout</classname>):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1954
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      ".v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-marginexample .v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-margin-left   {padding-left:   200px;}\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-marginexample .v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-margin-right  {padding-right:  100px;}\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-marginexample .v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-margin-top    {padding-top:    50px; }\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-marginexample .v-<emphasis>horizontallayout</emphasis>-margin-bottom {padding-bottom: 25px; }"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1956
#, no-c-format
msgid "The resulting margins are shown in <xref linkend=\"figure.layout.margin\"/> below. The two ways produce identical margins."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1976
#, no-c-format
msgid "The CSS style names for the margin widths for <methodname>setMargin()</methodname> consist of the specific layout name plus <literal>-margin-left</literal> and so on. The CSS style names for CSS-only margins consist of the specific layout name plus <literal>-margin</literal>. Below, the style rules are given for <classname>VerticalLayout</classname>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:1986
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<?pocket-size 75% ?>/* Alternative 1: CSS only style */\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>verticallayout</emphasis>-margin {\n"
      "    padding-left:   ___px;\n"
      "    padding-right:  ___px;\n"
      "    padding-top:    ___px;\n"
      "    padding-bottom: ___px;\n"
      "}\n"
      "/* Alternative 2: CSS rules to be enabled in code */\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>verticallayout</emphasis>-margin-left   {padding-left:   ___px;}\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>verticallayout</emphasis>-margin-right  {padding-right:  ___px;}\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>verticallayout</emphasis>-margin-top    {padding-top:    ___px;}\n"
      ".v-<emphasis>verticallayout</emphasis>-margin-bottom {padding-bottom: ___px;}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:1993
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom Layouts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:1995
#, no-c-format
msgid "While it is possible to create almost any typical layout with the standard layout components, it is sometimes best to separate the layout completely from code. With the <classname>CustomLayout</classname> component, you can write your layout as a template in XHTML that provides locations of any contained components. The layout template is included in a theme. This separation allows the layout to be designed separately from code, for example using WYSIWYG web designer tools such as Adobe Dreamweaver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2005
#, no-c-format
msgid "A template is a HTML file located under <filename>layouts</filename> folder under a theme folder under the <filename>WebContent/VAADIN/themes/</filename> folder, for example, <filename>WebContent/VAADIN/themes/<emphasis>themename/layouts/mylayout.html</emphasis></filename>. (Notice that the root path <filename>WebContent/VAADIN/themes/</filename> for themes is fixed.) A template can also be provided dynamically from an <classname>InputStream</classname>, as explained below. A template includes <literal>&lt;div&gt;</literal> elements with a <parameter>location</parameter> attribute that defines the location identifier. All custom layout HTML-files must be saved using UTF-8 character encoding."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:2018
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<?pocket-size 75% ?>&lt;table width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\"&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;tr height=\"100%\"&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;td&gt;\n"
      "      &lt;table align=\"center\"&gt;\n"
      "        &lt;tr&gt;\n"
      "          &lt;td align=\"right\"&gt;User&amp;nbsp;name:&lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "          &lt;td&gt;<emphasis role=\"strong\">&lt;div location=\"username\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</emphasis>&lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "        &lt;/tr&gt;\n"
      "        &lt;tr&gt;\n"
      "          &lt;td align=\"right\"&gt;Password:&lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "          &lt;td&gt;<emphasis role=\"strong\">&lt;div location=\"password\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</emphasis>&lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "        &lt;/tr&gt;\n"
      "      &lt;/table&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;/tr&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;tr&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;td align=\"right\" colspan=\"2\"&gt;\n"
      "      <emphasis role=\"strong\">&lt;div location=\"okbutton\"&gt;</emphasis>&lt;/div&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;/td&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;/tr&gt;\n"
      "&lt;/table&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2020
#, no-c-format
msgid "The client-side engine of Vaadin will replace contents of the location elements with the components. The components are bound to the location elements by the location identifier given to <methodname>addComponent()</methodname>, as shown in the example below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:2027
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
      "<?pocket-size 70% ?><![CDATA[// Have a Panel where to put the custom layout.\n"
      "Panel panel = new Panel(\"Login\");\n"
      "panel.setSizeUndefined();\n"
      "main.addComponent(panel);\n"
      "\n"
      "// Create custom layout from \"layoutname.html\" template.\n"
      "CustomLayout custom = new CustomLayout(\"layoutname\");\n"
      "custom.addStyleName(\"customlayoutexample\");\n"
      "\n"
      "// Use it as the layout of the Panel.\n"
      "panel.setContent(custom);\n"
      "\n"
      "// Create a few components and bind them to the location tags\n"
      "// in the custom layout.\n"
      "TextField username = new TextField();\n"
      "custom.addComponent(username, \"username\");\n"
      "\n"
      "TextField password = new TextField();\n"
      "custom.addComponent(password, \"password\");\n"
      "\n"
      "Button ok = new Button(\"Login\");\n"
      "custom.addComponent(ok, \"okbutton\");]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2029
#, no-c-format
msgid "The resulting layout is shown below in <xref linkend=\"figure.layout.customlayout\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: part1-layout.xml:2034
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example of a Custom Layout Component"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2045
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use <methodname>addComponent()</methodname> also to replace an existing component in the location given in the second parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2050
#, no-c-format
msgid "In addition to a static template file, you can provide a template dynamically with the <classname>CustomLayout</classname> constructor that accepts an <classname>InputStream</classname> as the template source. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:2056
#, no-c-format
msgid "<![CDATA[new CustomLayout(new ByteArrayInputStream(\"<b>Template</b>\".getBytes()));]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: part1-layout.xml:2058
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>or</para>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: part1-layout.xml:2060
#, no-c-format
msgid "<![CDATA[new CustomLayout(new FileInputStream(file));]]>"
msgstr ""

